; Regression test for issue #1794: price syntax/--revalued/--gains mysteries
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/1794
;
; The issue reports that:
; 1. @/@@ price syntax records lot dates, but {}/{{}}/{=}/{{=}} does not
; 2. --revalued-only -V suppresses all register output when no price history exists
;
; Commodity prices for ETC (not ETF, so no market price for ETF positions)
P 2019-01-01 ETC  11 EUR
P 2019-02-01 ETC  12 EUR

2019-01-11
    (A)    2 ETF @ 10 EUR

2019-01-12
    (B)    2 ETF @@ 20 EUR

2019-01-13
    (C)    2 ETF {10 EUR}

2019-01-14
    (D)    2 ETF {{20 EUR}}

2019-01-15
    (F)    2 ETF @= 10 EUR

2019-01-16
    (G)    2 ETF @@= 20 EUR

2019-01-17
    (H)    2 ETF {=10 EUR}

2019-01-18
    (I)    2 ETF {{=20 EUR}}

2019-02-15
    (J)    2 ETF

; Bug: @/@@ records lot dates but {}/{{}}/{=}/{{=}} does not
; The @/@@ syntaxes show [2019/01/NN] dates in --lots output,
; but {}/{{}}/{=}/{{=}} syntaxes only show lot prices without dates.
test bal --flat --no-total --lots
2 ETF {EUR10} [2019/01/11]  A
2 ETF {EUR10} [2019/01/12]  B
       2 ETF {EUR10}  C
       2 ETF {EUR10}  D
2 ETF {=EUR10} [2019/01/15]  F
2 ETF {=EUR10} [2019/01/16]  G
      2 ETF {=EUR10}  H
      2 ETF {=EUR10}  I
               2 ETF  J
end test

; Bug: --revalued-only -V suppresses all output even when ETF positions exist.
; Since ETF has no price history (only ETC does), -V cannot convert ETF to a
; market value, so --revalued-only -V produces no output at all.
; Expected: either an error or revalued postings; actual: empty output.
test reg --revalued-only -V
end test
